OL,3,CWhy do women suffer more in the heat?
OL,5,FWomen generally sweat less than men,
OL,6,Fbecause they have a lower baseline
OL,7,Finternal temperature, so it takes
OL,8,Flonger to reach the temperature needed
OL,9,Fto activate the body's sweating
OL,10,Fmechanism.
OL,12,FThis can make women feel hotter, as
OL,13,Fsweating is one of the body's key ways
OL,14,Fof cooling itself.
OL,16,FSmaller bodies
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1782350285
OL,3,CWhy do women suffer more in the heat?
OL,5,FAnd then there are the more general
OL,6,Fdifferences of how men and women are
OL,7,Fbuilt, with women typically having
OL,8,Fsmaller bodies, less blood volume,
OL,9,Fsmaller hearts and lower levels of
OL,10,Fhaemoglobin, which carries oxygen
OL,11,Faround the bloodstream.
OL,13,F"What that means is the cardiovascular
OL,14,Fsystem has less reserve to maintain
OL,15,Four blood pressure and to pump blood
OL,16,Fto the skin for cooling, because as
OL,17,Fthe blood comes nearer the surface of
OL,18,Fthe skin, that's how we emit the
OL,19,Fheat," Dr Patel said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
