PN,31307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1782350285
OL,3,CWhy do women suffer more in the heat?
OL,5,FWhile they have a lower core
OL,6,Ftemperature, women do have a higher
OL,7,Fskin temperature, which can contribute
OL,8,Fto feeling hotter.
OL,10,FAltogether those factors can lead to
OL,11,Ffeeling dizzy, fatigued and heat
OL,12,Fintolerant.
OL,14,FSpecific medical conditions
OL,16,FThere is a long list of medical
OL,17,Fconditions that are more prevalent in
OL,18,Fwomen, including thyroid condition,
OL,19,Flupus and iron deficiency, which can
OL,20,Fmake hot temperatures harder to handle.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
